[This incident highlights the desirability of routine vaccination of
all domestic animals (not an expensive option) where there is risk of
contact of pets with raccoons and other wild animals. Further
information regarding the outcome of the search for the suspected
rabid raccoon, and the extent of control of raccoon rabies by baited
vaccine in Delaware would be appreciated.

A map of the state of Delaware showing the location of Wilmington can
be accessed at:
<http://www.united-states-map.org/map/delaware-map.gif>. The
HealthMap/ProMED-mail of the USA is available at:
<http://healthmap.org/r/009V>. - Mod.CP]
